title: Pennsylvania High Court Rejects Lawsuit Challenging Election
sub_head: Justices throw out a lower court’s order preventing state from certifying dozens of contests
body:
HARRISBURG, Pa.—Pennsylvania’s highest court on Saturday night threw out a lower court’s order preventing the state from certifying dozens of contests on its Nov. 3 election ballot in the latest lawsuit filed by Republicans who are attempting to block the victory of President-elect Joe Biden in the battleground state.
